Write a c program to search for a character in a string. It will print the index of the element, if it is found. Otherwise, it will print "Not found."
Write a c program to count the frequency of a character in a string.
Write a c program to count the number of capital letters and small letters in a string.
Write a c program to count the number of vowels, consonants, digits, white-spaces, and special characters.
Write a c program to count alphanumeric characters in a string. Note that alphanumeric characters are a combination of alphabetic and numeric characters. Your program will print 8 for this string "<html></html>".
Write a c program to calculate the length of a string.
Write a c program to add three strings.
Write a c program to copy a string to another string.
Write a c program to reverse a string.
Write a c program to check whether a string is a palindrome or not